'''Nonkululeko Merina Cheryl Nyembezi-Heita''', also '''Nku''' (born 22 March 1960), is a South African business executive who has been active in steel, telecommunications and finance.<ref name=fmsa>{{cite web|url=http://fsma.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Dr-Scott-Couper_AGM-2015.pdf|title=A Sampling: Artefact, Document and Image|publisher=FSMA: Forum for School Museums & Archives|author=Couper, Scott|date=18 March 2015|accessdate=14 February 2016 |language=}}</ref><ref name=ichorcoal>{{cite web|url=http://www.ichorcoal.com/media/16873/12-Management_Board_Nominee_Nonkululeko_Nyembezi-Heita_IchorCoal_NV.pdf|title=Mrs. Nonkululeko Nyembezi-Heita|publisher=IchorCoal|accessdate=14 February 2016 |language=}}</ref> Since March 2014, she has been [[Chief Executive Officer|CEO]] of the Dutch mining group, IchorCoal N.V.<ref name=bb>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=10387953&privcapId=6866114|title=Nonkululeko Merina Cheryl Nyembezi-Heita BSc (Hons) (Elec Eng), MSc (Elec Eng), MBA|publisher=BloombergBusiness|accessdate=15 February 2016 |language=}}</ref>
==Biography== Nyembezi-Heita was born in [[Pietermaritzburg]], South Africa, where her father was an attorney. She has an older brother (Manqoba Nyembezi) and a younger sister(Ndo Nyembezi). Brought up in a Methodist family, she attended a [[Bantu peoples|Bantu]] primary school in [[Clermont, KwaZulu-Natal]], before embarking on her secondary school education at [[Inanda Seminary School]] near [[Durban]]. She obtained exceptionally good results in science and maths, becoming the top student in South Africa in her Junior Certificate year. After receiving her Senior Certificate, she was awarded an Awarded Anglo American Corporation Open Scholarship.<ref name=fmsa/> She went on to graduate in electrical engineering at the [[University of Manchester Institute of Science and Technology]] and earned a Master of Science degree from the [[California Institute of Technology]]. She also has an [[Master of Business Administration|MBA]] from the [[Open University Business School]].<ref name=ichorcoal/><ref name=bb/>
After first working in various positions with [[IBM]] in the United States and South Africa (1986–98), she moved to [[Alliance Capital Management]] where she headed financial services.<ref name=ichorcoal/> In 2008, she was appointed executive director of [[ArcelorMittal|ArcelorMittal South Africa]] where she remained for six years. In March 2014, she joined IchorCoal as CEO. Nyembezi-Heita has also served on the boards of several other companies.<ref name=bb/>
In 2012, Nyembezi-Heita was listed 97th in [[Forbes list of The World's 100 Most Powerful Women]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/power-women/gallery/nonkululeko-nyembezi-heita|title=Nyembezi-Heita|publisher=Forbes|accessdate=15 February 2016 |language=}}</ref>
